  "interpretation": [
    "MORI routed VJP is still the main MoE backward wall at both EP4 and EP8.",
    "Local padded VJP math is the largest single child bucket (~4.06s mean per profiled step), so grouped GEMM/SwiGLU remains a real target.",
    "The new split also exposes large host metadata synchronization: dispatch_x total_recv.item is ~1.6-1.7s mean; topk dummy total_recv.item is ~1.0-1.1s mean.",
    "dispatch_x.get_dispatch_src_token_pos is smaller on EP8 (~135ms mean) than EP4 (~375ms mean), but still not zero.",
    "combine_dx Python call is short on CPU, but the gpu_user_annotation under combine_dx.call is ~1.0-1.1s mean, so combine device work/wait is another bucket.",
    "Dense linear owner tags are sub-second all-rank totals in this profile and are not the main backward wall compared with MORI routed VJP."
  ],
